Jermain Defoe scored the winner for Sunderland in the Wear-Tyne derby . 
  Newcastle keeper Tim Krul congratulated Defoe on his goal before half-time . 
  Sportsmail's Jamie Carragher claimed Krul made a mistake by smiling and fist-pumping the striker . 
  Sunderland beat Newcastle 1-0 at the Stadium of Light in the Premier League . 
  Dick Advocaat says Jermain Defoe has set his side on the way to survival . 
 